{"word":"ἄρτι","slug":"ἄρτι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄρτι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>*<a href='S:ἄρω'><el>ἄρω</el></a>\n<p/><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>just, exactly</i>,<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>of the present, <i>just now, even now</i>, with <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of the past, <i>just now, just</i>, with <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> and <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>in late writers of the future, <i>just now, presently</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}